{
  "title": "AD #9 · Free College (Path C · Evaluate)",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "translation": "Claire 和 Paul 都说中了部分真相，但他们「免费还是不免费」的问法太粗。",
      "phrases": ["Both Claire and Paul", "catch part of the truth,", "but their \"free or not\" way", "of framing the question", "is too sharp."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "我反对所有人都上免费大学，而是支持更有针对性的方案：低收入学生免学费，其他学生用按收入还款的贷款。",
      "phrases": ["I would argue against", "full free college for everyone,", "and instead support", "a more targeted plan:", "free tuition", "for low-income students,", "plus income-based loans", "for everyone else."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "Claire 说机会重要，是对的。",
      "phrases": ["Claire is right", "that access matters."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "但当所有人免学费时，付得起的家庭也拿到了这笔福利。",
      "phrases": ["But when tuition is free", "for everyone,", "families who could easily pay", "also get the benefit."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "在德国，富裕家庭和贫困家庭拿到的补贴一样多，本该帮更需要学生的公共资金被摊薄到了全体人口上。",
      "phrases": ["In Germany,", "wealthy parents", "get the same subsidy", "as poor ones,", "and public money", "that could have helped", "needier students", "gets spread thin", "across the whole population."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "与此同时，正如 Paul 担心的，入学人数上升而教室数量不变。",
      "phrases": ["At the same time,", "as Paul worries,", "enrollment goes up", "while the number of classrooms", "does not."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "课堂拥挤、质量下降在几个欧洲国家已经出现。",
      "phrases": ["Crowded lectures", "and falling quality", "have already shown up", "in several European countries."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "一个更好的方案对准真正的问题。",
      "phrases": ["A better plan", "targets the real problem."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "来自低收入家庭的学生不交钱，真正的门槛被搬走。",
      "phrases": ["Students from", "low-income families", "pay nothing,", "which removes", "the real barrier."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "其他学生贷款，收入过了门槛才开始还——澳大利亚多年来就是这个模式。",
      "phrases": ["Other students take loans", "and only start paying back", "after their income", "passes a set level —", "this is the model", "Australia has used for years."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "公平被保留，富裕家庭不再搭便车，学生也能感到自己付出的价值。",
      "phrases": ["Fairness is kept,", "wealthy families stop free-riding,", "and students still feel", "the value of what", "they are paying for."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "「全民免费」听着公平。一个精细的方案其实更公平。",
      "phrases": ["\"Free for all\" sounds fair.", "A careful plan", "is actually fairer."]
    }
  ]
}
